value.value: Melanoma-associated antigen 2 (314 aa, ~35 kDa) is encoded by the human MAGEA2 and MAGEA2B genes. This protein plays a role in the modulation of p53-dependent signaling pathways.

Human SEPTIN4 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q22 and is approximately 20 kb in length. This allele, which encodes septin-4 protein, plays a role in both GTP hydrolysis and the structure of the cytoskeleton.

Septin-4 (478 aa, ~55 kDa) is encoded by the human SEPTIN4 gene. This protein is involved in both cytoskeletal structure and GTP hydrolysis.
This gene plays a role in the regulation of histone acetylation.

Human HDAC10 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 22q13.31 and is approximately 6 kb in length. This allele, which encodes histone deacetylase 10 protein, is involved in both transcriptional regulation and histone deacetylation.
Histone deacetylase 10 (669 aa, ~71 kDa) is encoded by the human HDAC10 gene. This protein plays a role in both the deacetylation of histones and transcriptional regulation.

label.value: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor Superfamily Member 10C

value.value: Tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 10C (259 aa, ~27 kDa) is encoded by the human TNFRSF10C gene. This protein is involved in both binding to tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 10 and the inhibition of apoptosis.
This gene may enhance ubiquitin ligase activity.

Human MAGEB18 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of Xp21.3 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes melanoma-associated antigen B18 protein, may enhance ubiquitin ligase activity.
Melanoma-associated antigen B18 (343 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human MAGEB18 gene. This protein may enhance ubiquitin ligase activity.
This gene may play a role in embryonal development, tumor transformation, or tumor progression.

Human MAGEC1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of Xq26 and is approximately 6 kb in length. This allele, which encodes melanoma-associated antigen C1 protein, may be involved in embryonal development, tumor transformation, or tumor progression.
Melanoma-associated antigen C1 (1142 aa, ~124 kDa) is encoded by the human MAGEC1 gene. This protein may play a role in embryonal development, tumor transformation, or tumor progression.

Human MAGEC2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of Xq27 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes melanoma-associated antigen C2 protein, may enhance ubiquitin ligase activity. The gene is frequently expressed in head and neck carcinomas, breast carcinomas, non-small-cell lung carcinomas, and sarcomas.
Melanoma-associated antigen C2 (373 aa, ~41 kDa) is encoded by the human MAGEC2 gene. This protein may enhance ubiquitin ligase activity.
This gene plays a role in transcriptional repression.

Human HES3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p36.31 and is approximately 1 kb in length. This allele, which encodes transcription factor HES-3 protein, is involved in the negative regulation of transcription.
Transcription factor HES-3 (186 aa, ~20 kDa) is encoded by the human HES3 gene. This protein plays a role in the repression of transcription.
This gene plays a role in the modulation of transcription.

Human HES6 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2q37.3 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes transcription cofactor HES-6 protein, is involved in the regulation of gene expression.
Transcription cofactor HES-6 (224 aa, ~24 kDa) is encoded by the human HES6 gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of transcription factor activity.
This gene is involved in both transcriptional regulation and Notch signaling pathways.

Human HEY2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6q21 and is approximately 14 kb in length. This allele, which encodes hairy/enhancer-of-split related with YRPW motif protein 2, plays a role in both Notch signal transduction and transcriptional repression.
This gene plays a role in the induction of apoptosis.

Human NLRP1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17p13.2 and is approximately 120 kb in length. This allele, which encodes NACHT, LRR and PYD domains-containing protein 1, is involved in apoptosis induction. Mutations in the gene are associated with vitiligo-associated multiple autoimmune disease susceptibility 1.

label.value: Hairy/Enhancer-Of-Split Related With YRPW Motif Protein 2

value.value: Hairy/enhancer-of-split related with YRPW motif protein 2 (337 aa, ~36 kDa) is encoded by the human HEY2 gene. This protein is involved in both the negative regulation of gene expression and Notch-dependent signaling.

label.value: NACHT, LRR and PYD Domains-Containing Protein 1

value.value: NACHT, LRR and PYD domains-containing protein 1 (1473 aa, ~166 kDa) is encoded by the human NLRP1 gene. This protein plays a role in the induction of apoptosis.
This gene plays a role in nucleoside transport.

Human NCR2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.1 and is approximately 15 kb in length. This allele, which encodes natural cytotoxicity triggering receptor 2 protein plays a role in natural killer cell function.
